'''安布罗斯·格溫莱特·比尔斯'''（{{lang|en|Ambrose Gwinnett Bierce}}；{{bd|1842年|6月24日|1914年}}）
<ref name="online-literature.com">{{Cite web|title=Ambrose Bierce|url=http://www.online-literature.com/bierce/|accessdate=2019-11-06|work=Biography and Works. Search Texts, Read Online. Discuss.|archive-date=2021-01-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210115092043/http://www.online-literature.com/bierce/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Floyd18">{{cite book|last1=Floyd|first1=E. Randall|title=The Good, the Bad, and the Mad: Some Weird People in American History|url=https://archive.org/details/goodbadmadsomewe0000floy|year=1999|publisher=Barnes & Noble Publishing, Inc.|location=New York|isbn=978-0-7607-6600-2|page=[https://archive.org/details/goodbadmadsomewe0000floy/page/18 18]}}</ref>，或译为「安卜罗斯·皮尔斯」，是一位[[美国|美国]][[记者|记者]]、[[短篇小说|短篇小说]]、[[传说|传说]]与讽刺小说[[作家|作家]]。著名作品有短篇小说《[[鹰溪桥上|鹰溪桥上]]》（{{lang|en|''An Occurrence at Owl Creek Bridge''}}）和讽刺小说《[[魔鬼辞典|魔鬼辞典]]》（{{lang|en|''The Devil's Dictionary''}}）等。

1913年，前往墨西哥。於當時的[[墨西哥革命|墨西哥革命]]中失蹤。<ref>Bierce letter from Chihuahua to Blanche Partington dated December 26, 1913. Printed in A Much Misunderstood Man: Selected Letters of Ambrose Bierce, S. T. Joshi and David E. Schultz, eds. Columbus: Ohio State University Press, 2003, pp. 244–46.</ref>

==名言==
{{cquote|爱国主义：名词，一堆随时可以被任何野心家所点燃，去照亮他的名字的易燃垃圾。在[[塞缪尔·约翰逊|约翰逊博士]]著名的字典中，爱国主义被定义为无赖最后的避难所。带着对这位开明但有缺陷的词典编纂家应有的敬意，我斗胆认为爱国主义应该是无赖的第一个避难所。（Patriotism, n. Combustible rubbish ready to the torch of any one ambitious to illuminate his name. In Dr. Johnson's famous dictionary patriotism is defined as the last resort of a scoundrel. With all due respect to an enlightened but inferior lexicographer I beg to submit it is the first.）|安布罗斯·格溫莱特·比尔斯，1911|《魔鬼辞典》}}

